@jujoramos @jinmeiliao 
> @mhansonp: just FYI, I have an old [PR](https://github.com/apache/geode/pull/5393) opened (draft as the feature is not yet implemented) to test the backward compatibility of the `clear` operation, it might be useful for your current work.

I looked at the Juan's code and it looked like the code I really needed (the core of the tests) had not been implemented yet, so it was not as much help as I hoped.

@mivanac Thanks for incorporating my suggestions. Three were incomplete, though, so I'd like to request tweaks.
Two occurrences of "in milliseconds" should have a comma afterwards: "in milliseconds,".
One occurrence of "whose members runtime configurations" should have an apostrophy after " members " to get the plural possessive " members' ". Final form should be "whose members' runtime configurations" .

> @albertogpz some engineers pointed me at `DualServerSNIAcceptanceTest` to possibly be a template to help with testing this.
> I will admit I'm not across anything done in this test, maybe @Bill could provide some guidance if you have more questions

@kohlmu-pivotal Great, thanks! I will take a look at that test and if @Bill wants to comment, he is more than welcome.
